## Tech Stack & Architecture - **Ultra-Optimized**

### Core Technologies
- **Framework**: Next.js 15.5.3 with App Router (Static Generation)
- **Runtime**: React 19.1.1
- **Language**: TypeScript 5.0.2
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.1.9 (minimal, optimized)
- **Fonts**: System font stack (zero external requests)
- **UI Components**: Custom components (no external UI libraries)
- **Package Manager**: pnpm
- **Deployment**: Vercel (globally cached)
- **Analytics**: Vercel Analytics + Speed Insights

### Key Pages (4 total)
- `app/page.tsx`: Homepage with dual service overview
- `app/layout.tsx`: Root layout with comprehensive meta tags and analytics
- `app/services/page.tsx`: Detailed service offerings (advisory + talent)
- `app/clients/page.tsx`: Client showcase and testimonials
- `app/creations/page.tsx`: Our own product creations and exits

### **Performance Architecture**
- **Bundle Size**: 102kB shared JS + ~900B per page
- **Dependencies**: 6 production packages only (vs 67+ before optimization)
- **Static Generation**: All pages pre-rendered for instant loading
- **System Fonts**: Zero external font requests for maximum speed
- **Mobile-First**: Responsive hamburger menu, touch-optimized

## Development Guidelines

### Code Quality Standards

#### ⚠️ MANDATORY: Pre-Commit Linting
**ALWAYS run these commands before committing ANY changes:**

```bash
# Step 1: Auto-fix all possible issues
pnpm run fix-all

# Step 2: Verify everything passes
pnpm run check-all
```

**Never commit code that fails linting or formatting checks.**

#### Available Quality Commands
```bash
pnpm run format         # Format with Prettier
pnpm run lint           # ESLint (warnings allowed)
pnpm run lint:strict    # ESLint with zero warnings
pnpm run lint:fix       # Auto-fix ESLint issues
pnpm run type-check     # TypeScript validation
pnpm run check-all      # Full validation pipeline
pnpm run fix-all        # Auto-fix + validation
```

### Code Style Preferences

#### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript settings
- Prefer explicit types for function parameters and return types
- Use proper typing for React components and props
- Avoid `any` types - use `unknown` or specific types

#### React/Next.js
- Use App Router patterns (not Pages Router)
- Prefer Server Components when possible
- Use Client Components (`'use client'`) only when necessary (header menu only)
- Always use Next.js `<Link />` component instead of `<a>` tags for internal navigation
- Follow React 19 patterns and best practices

#### Performance Requirements
- **System fonts only** - never add Google Fonts or external font requests
- **Minimal dependencies** - avoid adding UI libraries, use custom components
- **Mobile-first responsive design** with hamburger menu
- **Optimize for Core Web Vitals** (LCP < 1.2s, FID < 100ms, CLS = 0)

#### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes (minimal, optimized build)
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Use semantic HTML elements
- **System font stack**: `font-mono` class for monospace text

#### Import Organization
```typescript
// 1. Node/built-in modules
import { useState } from 'react'

// 2. External libraries (minimal)
import Link from 'next/link'

// 3. Internal modules
import SiteHeader from '@/components/site-header'
```

### Performance Considerations
- **NO external font requests** - use system fonts only
- **Minimal JavaScript** - current bundle ~102kB shared
- **Static generation** for all pages (no server-side rendering)
- **Optimized images** using Next.js `<Image />` component
- **Aggressive caching** via Vercel configuration
- Monitor Core Web Vitals through Vercel Speed Insights

### SEO Requirements
- Maintain comprehensive meta tags in all page files
- Use semantic HTML structure
- Ensure accessibility compliance (ARIA, proper headings)
- **Structured data** (JSON-LD) in layout.tsx
- **Sitemap.xml** and **robots.txt** in public folder

